  "name": "RPlog_Dangerous_Games",
  "title": "Dangerous Games",
  "summary": "Lord Smitherbodkins hosts an opulent, Corellia-themed sabacc gala at his stately manor, drawing a mix of Imperials, locals, and grifters. The boorish COMPNOR senior strategist Giles Pendleton makes a swaggering entrance and sits down to play alongside the host, the gambler Harmon, and the disguised doctor Lynae 'Lyn' Cassius, while the scruffy Corellian con man Alac Y'all and Imperial corpsman Calyx Drogyn join the table amid much banter. When Giles makes a thousand-credit bet, Alac draws a concealed DL-44 and guns the Imperial official down at point-blank range, then bolts through the chaos, dodging a thrown fruit basket from the Rattataki Leate and escaping over the wall despite security and a stray battle-hound. Lynae, Calyx, and Harmon confirm Giles is dead while Smitherbodkins smoothly manages the scene as Imperial troops belatedly storm in to secure the body. The evening ends with the late, regal chamberlain Mara Shinomiya arriving just as the corpse is carried out, offering theatrical condolences as Smitherbodkins leads her away.",
